cv_definitions.label: CL
cv_definitions.name: The Cell Ontology is a structured controlled vocabulary for cell types in animals.

cv_definitions.label: EDAM
cv_definitions.name: The ontology of data analysis and management

cv_definitions.label: HGNC
cv_definitions.name: The HGNC (HUGO Gene Nomenclature Committee) provides an approved gene name and symbol (short-form abbreviation) for each known human gene.  All approved symbols are stored in the HGNC database, and each symbol is unique. HGNC identifiers refer to records in the HGNC symbol database.

cv_definitions.label: MONDO
cv_definitions.name: A global community effort to harmonize multiple disease resources to yield a coherent merged ontology.

cv_definitions.label: NCBITAXON
cv_definitions.name: National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI) Organismal Classification

cv_definitions.label: ROR
cv_definitions.name:
ROR (Research Organization Registry) is a global, community-led registry
of open persistent identifiers for research organizations. ROR is jointly
operated by California Digital Library, Crossref, and Datacite.
